{"type":"text","timestamp":1773245133125,"sessionID":"ses_3225b067cffeiaaQ6ABO3MVd2p","part":{"id":"prt_cdda55e13001CfuCqJ9xW8b5fS","sessionID":"ses_3225b067cffeiaaQ6ABO3MVd2p","messageID":"msg_cdda54d6d001g6D6KL4aIFgcFa","type":"text","text":"Now let me implement the `--version` / `-V` flag. I need to:\n\n1. Handle `--version` and `-V` as top-level commands (like `--help` / `-h`) before arg parsing consumes `--version` as an option\n2. Read version from package.json\n3. Print it and exit\n\nLooking at the code, `--version` is already parsed as a flag that takes a value argument (for the `upgrade` command's `--version <tag>`). I need to handle `--version` and `-V` as the *first argument* (command position) to print the version, while preserving the existing `--version <tag>` behavior for the `upgrade` command.\n\nLet me look at how the arg parsing works more carefully:","time":{"start":1773245133124,"end":1773245133124}}}
