{"type":"text","timestamp":1773245247727,"sessionID":"ses_3225b067cffeiaaQ6ABO3MVd2p","part":{"id":"prt_cdda71ce9002l05VvqDLBZ1nVf","sessionID":"ses_3225b067cffeiaaQ6ABO3MVd2p","messageID":"msg_cdda7108e001GAa3u0VEv5ww56","type":"text","text":"All tasks complete. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n## Summary\n\n### Subtask 1: `--version` / `-V` flag (`feat(cli-ux-polish)`)\n- **Problem:** `wombo --version` showed \"Unknown command\" and dumped the full help text\n- **Fix:** Added early handling in `main()` for `--version` and `-V` as the command, reading version from `package.json` and printing `wombo 0.0.3`. Also added documentation to the help text.\n- **Commit:** `6d205f4`\n\n### Subtask 2: Fix misleading `--all-ready` message (`fix(cli-ux-polish)`)\n- **Problem:** `launch --all-ready` with no launchable features said \"Use --all-ready to see all available\" — contradicting the flag already being passed\n- **Fix:** Made the error message context-aware. When `--all-ready` is active, shows \"No launchable features found. All features may be done, cancelled, or have unmet dependencies.\" Otherwise, shows the original suggestion to use `--all-ready`.\n- **Commit:** `42bb26d`\n\n### Verification\n- `bun run typecheck` — passes cleanly\n- `bun run build` — passes cleanly (0.72 MB bundle in 15ms)","time":{"start":1773245247725,"end":1773245247725}}}
