\n  *   wombo features archive [feature-id] [--dry-run]\n  *   wombo features show <feature-id>\n  *   wombo help\n+ *   wombo --version\n  */\n \n import { resolve } from \"node:path\";\n@@ -319,6 +320,7 @@ Launch Options:\n   --max-retries N          Max retries per agent (default: from config)\n \n General:\n+  --version, -V            Print version and exit\n   --force                  Force overwrite (e.g., for init) / skip prompts (e.g., for upgrade)\n   --output <fmt>           Output format: text (default on TTY) or json (default when piped)\n   -o <fmt>                 Alias for --output\n@@ -393,6 +395,18 @@ async function main(): Promise<void> {\n   }\n \n   // Commands that don't need config loading\n+  if (args.command === \"--version\" || args.command === \"-V\") {\n+    const pkgPath = resolve(import.meta.dir, \"..\", \"package.json\");\n+    try {\n+      const raw = readFileSync(pkgPath, \"utf-8\");\n+      const pkg = JSON.parse(raw);\n+      console.log(`wombo ${pkg.version}`);\n+    } catch {\n+      console.log(\"wombo (unknown version)\");\n+    }\n+    return;\n+  }\n+\n   if (args.command === \"help\" || args.command === \"--help\" || args.command === \"-h\") {\n     cmdHelp();\n     return;\n","exit":0,"description":"Check diff from main on index.ts","truncated":false},"time":{"start":1773246692943,"end":1773246692948}}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1773246692979,"sessionID":"ses_3224353f9ffe48zNky1jQ0HMD4","part":{"id":"prt_cddbcf5c6001ou9QgsoRxINwNC","sessionID":"ses_3224353f9ffe48zNky1jQ0HMD4","messageID":"msg_cddbce839001T0O78CULoiO48z","type":"text","text":"Let me now look more closely at the existing code. The `--version` flag is already partially handled in the `main()` function (lines 398-408) as a command, and also in `parseArgs` as a flag that takes a value argument (line 219-221 — that's for the `upgrade --version` flag). The issue is that `--version` / `-V` when used as the first argument (command position) is already handled. But when used as a flag in other positions (e.g., `wombo --version`), it works because `args[0]` would be `--version`. Let me verify the actual behavior described in the bug — \"shows Unknown command + full help dump.\"\n\nWait, looking again at the code: `parseArgs` sets `result.command = args[0] || \"help\"`. So `wombo --version` → `args[0] = \"--version\"` → `result.command = \"--version\"`. Then in `main()`, line 398 checks `if (args.command === \"--version\" || args.command === \"-V\")`. This already looks correct!\n\nBut wait — there's also the `-V` flag which is NOT handled in parseArgs as a command. Let me check if there's a conflict: the `--version` in parseArgs (line 219) is treated as a flag that takes a value (`result.version = args[++i]`), which is for the `upgrade` command's `--version` option. When `--version` is the first positional arg, it becomes the command, so the switch case at line 219 wouldn't be hit.\n\nLet me actually look at this more carefully. The issue says `wombo --version` shows \"Unknown command\" + full help dump. Let me trace through the code:\n\n1. `wombo --version` → `argv = ['bun', 'script', '--version']` → `args = ['--version']`\n2. `parseArgs` → `result.command = '--version'`\n3. In `main()`, line 398: `if (args.command === \"--version\" || args.command === \"-V\")` — this SHOULD match `--version`!\n\nHmm, actually it looks like the version flag IS already handled. Let me check if maybe the code was recently added but there's still an issue with `-V`. Let me look more carefully:\n\nActually, looking at the current code, both `--version` and `-V` are handled at lines 398-408. This appears to already be implemented. But wait, there might be a problem with the `--version` flag in `parseArgs` at line 219-221 — when `--version` is the first arg (command position), it's set as `result.command = \"--version\"`, so it never reaches line 219. But if someone types `wombo -V`, then `args[0] = \"-V\"` → `result.command = \"-V\"` → line 398 checks for this. This also looks handled.\n\nWait — let me re-examine. There may be an issue with `-V` not being handled in `parseArgs`. If `-V` is the first arg, `result.command = \"-V\"` and it hits the check at line 398. But what if someone does `wombo somecommand --version`? Then `--version` at line 219 would consume the next arg as a version string for upgrade. But that's a different scenario.\n\nActually, let me re-read the feature description more carefully: \"wombo --version shows Unknown command + full help dump. Should print the version from package.json and exit.\"\n\nPerhaps the code I'm seeing was added as part of this feature branch already? Let me check the git log:","time":{"start":1773246692978,"end":1773246692978}}}
